paragraphs.text: a voice like honey no one else could fill his shoes the time and the weather the headlines and the local news he lays it down with perfection and grace he's done by noon he goes home to his place where he sleeps and he waits for the night

just before midnight he gets up gets out of bed a can of red bull a tab of x to clear his head he shoots his cuffs now he's headed downtown picks up one life puts another one down and his body hums and the music's playing
